The paper deals with distributed algorithms for finding maximal matchings in graphs, which is a problem in distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of edge-colouring in the problem, which falls under the category of graph colouring (cs.AL). The paper presents lower and upper bounds on the complexity of the problem, which is a common theme in the subfield of theoretical computer science (cs.TH) and specifically in the study of distributed algorithms (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of anonymous graphs, which is a topic in the subfield of network science (cs.NI).
